The episode also showed us a nifty way to break across the language barrier. At first, Nem did not speak a word, but had Daniel read some Bayblonian texts on the wall. As he was translating aloud what was written into what was spoken, Nem was able to pick up the intricacies of the English lanuage. And even after that, Nem wasn't exactly speaking English with any fluency.

'Twas better than what happened in "Emancipation", where SG-1 was slowly trying to communicate with a native, unsure if he could even understand them, and then all of a sudden the native answers them in English, and SG-1 expresses relief of not having to communicate throughout the episode via subtitles that would appear magically at the bottom of their field of vision...
